The paper deals with spectrum sensing in cognitive radio, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithms are based on statistical covariances, which is a topic in statistics (cs.ST) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of multiple antennas, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP) and communication (cs.CR). Overall, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SI, cs.CR, and cs.LG.
